.SH NAME
\f4true\f1, \f4false\f1 \- provide truth values
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f4true\f1
.PP
\f4false\f1
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f4true\fP
does nothing, successfully.
\f4false\f1
does nothing, unsuccessfully.
They are typically used in input to
\f4sh\f1
such as:
.PP
.RS
\f4while true
.br
do
.RS
\f2command\fP
.RE
done\f1
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
\f4sh\fP(1)
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
\f4true\fP
has exit status zero,
\f4false\fP
nonzero.
